reviews.review_text:
Runnin' down the stairs... I'll never forget this one. I was usually about 1/4 of the way back the stage to the board, slightly to the left. But after the brake my college girlfriend Karla, (who I some times called my Dark Star girlfriend because we enjoyed my our second Dark Star here the previous year together, but she didn't really like that); insisted during the break that I stay for a while up on the grass just to do something different for a change; so I agreed to for the duration of "Scarlet Begonias". So during "Fire on the Mountain" I insisted we run down to the front. And I was so glad we did since we got down there for the first complete "Cryptical Envelopment" since I can't remember, at least 1971 or so!

     I still like the first show best,

     Augy
     San Diego
fun times i did not start my touring days untill 90 but these 80's shows are something else crisp clean downright enjoyable thanks 4 posting
